title: ‚ÄúFollowing‚Äù feed loaded with random posts
text:
This could‚Äôve been the successor microblogging social network. But it‚Äôs loaded with paper cuts. The latest is that the so-called ‚Äúfollowing‚Äù feed has become overrun with posts from accounts I don‚Äôt follow and the posts haven‚Äôt been reshared by accounts I do follow. Why are they in the ‚Äúfollowing‚Äù feed? Clearly, smarter people than me understand a different, less accurate definition of ‚Äúfollowing‚Äù to be superior to the one that sets up an expectation that one might see a feed with posts solely from or shared by accounts they follow.

Back to Ivory and Mastodon proper. Meta really blew it here.

Impossible to watch media on this app.  Can‚Äôt pause, or even rewind properly, and the mute button is only per one video.  You have to unmute every single video in your feed.  

Also the nesting is pure chaos.  If you expand a thread to read replies, it reorganises all the threads so you have to re-navigate back to your place.   App needs a lot of work my brothers.
